        <title type="html"><![CDATA[Document that the Enter key causes the “keypress” event to fire]]></title>
        <id>https://github.com/mdn/content/pull/37817</id>
        <link href="https://github.com/mdn/content/pull/37817"/>
        <updated>2025-01-27T03:16:05.000Z</updated>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<img src="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/194984?v=4" width="64" height="64" alt=""/><br/><p dir="auto">This change updates the page for the <code class="notranslate">keypress</code> event to match actual behavior in browsers — by changing the page to state that the event fires when the <kbd>Enter</kbd> key is pressed — not only when a key that produces a character value is pressed.</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="298091555" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/w3c/uievents/issues/183" data-hovercard-type="issue" data-hovercard-url="/w3c/uievents/issues/183/hovercard?comment_id=448091687&amp;comment_type=issue_comment" href="https://github.com/w3c/uievents/issues/183#issuecomment-448091687">w3c/uievents#183 (comment)</a></li>
<li><a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="624169701" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/w3c/uievents/issues/266" data-hovercard-type="issue" data-hovercard-url="/w3c/uievents/issues/266/hovercard?comment_id=1887917756&amp;comment_type=issue_comment" href="https://github.com/w3c/uievents/issues/266#issuecomment-1887917756">w3c/uievents#266 (comment)</a></li>
<li><a class="issue-link js-issue-link" data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="2809086190" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/w3c/uievents/issues/392" data-hovercard-type="pull_request" data-hovercard-url="/w3c/uievents/pull/392/hovercard" href="https://github.com/w3c/uievents/pull/392">w3c/uievents#392</a></li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Otherwise, without this change, the information on the <code class="notranslate">keypress</code> page incorrectly doesn’t match actual browser behavior — in that the page states that the <code class="notranslate">keypress</code> event fires <em>only</em> when a key that produces a character value are pressed, while in fact browsers also fire the event when the <kbd>Enter</kbd> key is pressed.</p>]]></content>
